<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">O’Brien</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-01-30"><hi rend="italic">January 30,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>At noon late crown prince proclaimed King Frederick VIII by prime
                            minister in presence of large concourse. Announcement received with
                            enthusiasm.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">O’Brien.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>